g.text: Two side-by-side diagrams illustrating borrowing a key from a right sibling versus merging with a left sibling to fix an underflow condition after deletion
Can right sibling spare a key?
Parent key moves down to underflow node
Right sibling's leftmost key moves up to parent
Right sibling's leftmost child moves to underflow node
Can left sibling spare a key?
Parent's separating key moves down to left sibling
All keys+children from underflow node move to left sibling
Merge complete, tree may need further balancing
